TERRAPULSE, INC. WILL CONTINUE PRODUCTION OF, AND DEVELOP METHODS TO CALIBRATE, THE TREE-CANOPY AND FOREST-DYNAMICS DATASET OVER MYANMAR FROM 1984 - 2018. THE GOAL OF THIS EFFORT WILL BE TO IMPROVE REPRESENTATION OF FOREST CHANGES, ESPECIALLY TRANSIENT LOSSES DUE TO CONVERSION OF NATURAL FOREST TO PLANTATIONS, WHICH WERE NOTED BY PROJECT PARTNERS IN YEAR 2. THE EFFORT WILL COMPRISE 3 ACTIVITIES:
 1. PRODUCTION OF AN UPDATED, BUT NOT YET EMPIRICALLY CALIBRATED, VERSION OF THE DATASET (SEPT 2019);
 2. DEVELOPMENT OF PROCESSES TO CALIBRATE TREE-CANOPY ESTIMATES BASED ON CANOPY-HEIGHT MODELS DERIVED FROM DRONE IMAGERY AND SUPPLIED BY SMITHSONIAN CONSERVATION BIOLOGY INSTITUTE (SCBI);
 3. APPLICATION OF CALIBRATION ALGORITHMS TO THE PENULTIMATE VERSION OF THE DATASET TO PRODUCE A FINAL, EMPIRICALLY CALIBRATED VERSION OF THE DATA (DECEMBER 2019).
 ACTIVITIES 2 AND 3 DEPEND ON PROVISION OF DRONE-BASED CANOPY-HEIGHT MODELS BY SCBI. THE FIRST OF THESE IS EXPECTED BY JUNE 1, 2019. DEVELOPMENT OF CALIBRATION ALGORITHMS CAN BEGIN SHORTLY AFTER RECEIPT OF THIS FIRST SAMPLE. TERRAPULSE WILL FURTHER DEVELOP AND APPLY CALIBRATION ALGORITHMS AFTER RECEIVING CANOPY-HEIGHT MODELS FROM OTHER SITES, 12 IN TOTAL, FROM SCBI ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1, 2019, CONTINUING THIS ACTIVITY UNTIL THE END OF THE PROJECT PERIOD.

